args: At this rate, we'll all drown!\nWe've gotta think of something!
We have to try to break through with the\nseacutter. We don't have the luxury of\nwaiting around to form a better plan.
Awfully risky gambit. Did you not hear\nme when I said I can't support us all?
The waves are too rough. Try to force your\nway against the current, and it could wind\nup just sucking you under.
I'm not entirely without a plan here. Setta,\nyou said you listen to the local fishermen's\ntales often, yes?
Can you recall them ever mentioning the\nplacement of any standing nets?
Huh? Uhhh... Actually, yeah! They told me\nnot to go near 'em 'cause it'd mess with\ntheir fishing. It was right around here, too!
Good. That tilts the odds in our favor a bit.\nSetta, you and I will do our best to head\nthere.
Can you go and signal the rescue boats,\nMarishiten? I trust you can get out so long\nas it's only you.
Guess I don't have much choice, given the\ncircumstances. Fine. But you owe me one.
I owe you far more than one, at this point.\nBut come, Setta! We must make ready to\ndepart. I'll be relying on your knowledge!
Uhhh, the spiky island's over there, so...\nRight! We need to go to the right! Augh,\nbut there's a big wave coming from that—
We'll push through it by force. Hold on\nto me, and don't let go! HaaaAAAH!
HOLY—! Did... Did we just jump over\nthat huge wave?!
I'll do whatever it takes to get you back to\nshore safely. Now, how's our course?
Good! We should be to the spot with the\nfishing nets soon. If we can hang on there\nuntil help comes—
GAH! Of all the times for a fiend to show!
Aaaaaugh! I can't, I can't!\nIeyasu, I'm scared!
Courage, Setta! We've no recourse but\nto face this foe head-on.
(You've helped me in so many ways this\nsummer. Now it's time to repay you for\nthat kindness.)
Things are about to get rougher than ever.\nI promise we'll be all right, so whatever\nyou do, don't let go!
Ieyasu, I can't... *inhale*\n...Okay. I trust you!
Thank you. Now, hang on!\nWyrmgrace Blade, secret technique—
We're through! Now, just a little further to\nthe nets!
...I guess this is goodbye for real, Ieyasu.
I fear you're right. We only just barely\nmade it back to land. I'm sorry that our\nfarewell must be so rushed.
That's not your fault. I'm the one who\nmessed up all your plans. But, um...
Would you accept these?\nIt's fine if you don't want them!
Yeah. They only grow in the back of that\ncave, so they're pretty rare. I wanted to,\nuh...say I'm sorry for yesterday.
But going to get them only made MORE\ntrouble for you, and they got all messed up\nfrom the salt water. B-but still, I just...
Of course I'll accept them!\nThank you for the lovely gift, Setta.
They're as beautiful as the sentiment\nbehind them. I shall dry and press them,\nso that I might cherish them forever.
They'll be a lovely souvenir of the summer\nI spent here, and a lasting symbol of our\nfriendship.
Aw. Thanks, Ieyasu. And, um...come back\nanytime! I'll clear my calendar for you!
It's a promise. In the meantime, be well,\nSetta.
The ship is all ready to depart,\nLord Ieyasu. This way, please.
...I take it you've found your experience\nhere both pleasant and worthwhile?
It's been wonderful. And, er...my apologies\nfor sneaking out of those parties.
Not at all. If anything, I was overzealous\nin my efforts to prevent anything untoward\nfrom happening to an honored guest.
You've certainly proven that you are a man\nboth brave and capable enough to weather\nanything the sea can throw at you.
And a man true to his friends, besides.\nPlease do pay us another visit soon.\nI promise you a more...relaxed reception.
I should like that very much, sir. Next\ntime, I would like to come as a simple\ntourist, together with my entourage.
I just heard the reports, my lord. Seems\nall the new systems you put in place after\nyour survey are integrating wonderfully.
The carpenters were abuzz working on your\nfaster, sturdier ship designs, and the shore\nfolk are coordinating well with the watch.
Thanks to their efforts, we've seen a sharp\ndecline in incidents along the coast.
The shogun seemed quite pleased. If local\nconditions continue to improve, he means\nto apply these policies elsewhere as well.
Goodness! You've done a remarkable job\nas always, Lord Ieyasu. Your efforts speak\nfor themselves, but...
The very fact that the results are so\nimpressive makes me fear you did\nnothing but work while you were there.

I was just thinking the same. Pretty sure
we told you it would've been okay—
preferred, even—for you to enjoy yourself
a bit more out there, my lord.
Worry not, Addis. I found ample time\nfor both work AND play.
Why, I even tasted an array of delicious\nlocal treats and made a lifelong friend\nalong the way.
Indeed it was. If you've the patience for it,\nI would be happy to regale you with a full\naccount of everything that happened.
It is the tale of a summer well-spent in the\ncompany of a most charming young man.
